    "body": "That's very similar to what I have right now in `ContractCompiler`:\r\n- A mapping from blocks to sets of variables declared in that block, such that they're freed in `endVisit(Block const&)`, which takes care of the general case.\r\n- A mapping from loops to sets of variables declared inside the loop up to the analyzed syntactic point. At `B1`, for example, the `while` would be pointing to `x` and `y`. The break tag then points to a piece of code that frees those variables only.",
